#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:9
msgid "title: Spread the Word"
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:13
msgid "## Spread the Word"
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:18
msgid ""
"We hope you love Ubuntu MATE as much as we do! If you do, we'd love for you to\n"
"share that excitement with others. Be creative! Put more green in your wardrobe.\n"
"When someone asks if you like coffee or tea, mention how you prefer MATE or\n"
"Ubuntu MATE. Here's a few other ideas."
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:20
msgid "### Social Media"
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:26
msgid ""
"This is definitely the easiest way to introduce your family, friends, and\n"
"random followers to Ubuntu MATE. Share a post from our [blog](/blog/). Follow\n"
"us at **[@ubuntumate](https://twitter.com/ubuntu_mate)**\n"
"and let our informative, GIF-filled posts inspire you to hit the 'Like' (and\n"
"maybe even the 'Retweet') button."
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:31
msgid ""
"Talk about Ubuntu MATE on your favorite IRC,\n"
"Mastodon, and Telegram groups, or your favorite Linux forum. Post an\n"
"influencer-worthy pic of your home office on Instagram, and use a filter to make\n"
"that green login screen pop. Make a Tik-Tok video so we all become Internet-famous."
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:33
msgid "### Merchandise"
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:39
msgid ""
"Sometimes, spreading the word doesn't take any words at all! A stylish Ubuntu\n"
"MATE polo, T-shirt, or hoodie can tell your friends, family, and coworkers you're\n"
" smart in your fashion AND Linux distro choices. Your morning cup of caffeine\n"
" can get you through your day and help spark a conversation. Find all these\n"
" goodies at our [shop](/shop/)."
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:41
msgid "### Reviews"
msgstr ""

#: pages/get-involved-spread-word.md:47
msgid ""
"Finally, one of the most useful ways of introducing people to Ubuntu MATE are\n"
"through members of the Linux community who give helpful and honest reviews of\n"
"Ubuntu MATE's strengths and weaknesses. We're fortunate to have a strong\n"
"reviewing community, and you can see some of these reviews on our\n"
"[Testimonials](/about/testimonials/) page. Community feedback has always helped\n"
"us improve Ubuntu MATE, and we're excited to hear from new voices with new insights."
msgstr ""
